docs.abstract: If your screen has become jumbled with too many open files, folders and programs to manage, you can quickly sort the pile.
docs.snippet: If your screen has become jumbled with too many open files, folders and programs to manage, you can quickly sort the pile.
docs.lead_paragraph: Q. When moving back and forth between laptop and external monitors and generally just having a ton of stuff open, I can’t find certain windows quickly in the clutter, or have trouble resizing them because I can’t reach the bottom corner with the mouse. Is there a quick way to snap these windows in line?

headline.main: Getting Your Desktop Windows in Order

docs.abstract: Barnes & Noble’s line of digital-book hardware offers a few ways to keep and store your expanding collection.
docs.snippet: Barnes & Noble’s line of digital-book hardware offers a few ways to keep and store your expanding collection.
docs.lead_paragraph: Q. On my Nook device, I have about 40 percent of my storage space left. I like some books quite a bit, so I don’t want to delete them. But where do these books go after all the memory is filled up or the device gets too old?

headline.main: Making More Room for a Nook Library

docs.abstract: Like many modern operating systems, macOS has a built-in spell checker that you can use or lose.
docs.snippet: Like many modern operating systems, macOS has a built-in spell checker that you can use or lose.
docs.lead_paragraph: Q. Now that I know how to turn off the automatic spelling correction on my iPhone, how can I turn it off on my Mac?

headline.main: How to Adjust Your Mac’s Spelling Controls

docs.abstract: Smartphone software can make it a little too easy to dial up your contacts whether you meant to or not, but you can help cut down on accidental calls.
docs.snippet: Smartphone software can make it a little too easy to dial up your contacts whether you meant to or not, but you can help cut down on accidental calls.
docs.lead_paragraph: Q. Can you explain “butt-dialing” or, more politely, pocket phoning/texting? What is happening in my pocket to trigger a call or text? How can I set my phone to make sure it doesn’t happen?

docs.abstract: An artist is under investigation for an exhibit intended to highlight China’s lack of privacy protections and a public sense of futility.
docs.snippet: An artist is under investigation for an exhibit intended to highlight China’s lack of privacy protections and a public sense of futility.
docs.lead_paragraph: BEIJING — Deng Yufeng wanted to create art that prods people to question their lack of data privacy. What better way, he reasoned, than to buy the personal information of more than 300,000 Chinese people off the internet and display it in a public exhibition?

headline.main: The Personal Data of 346,000 People, Hung on a Museum Wall
headline.print_headline: 346,000 People’s Data,  Displayed on a Wall

byline.original: By Sui-Lee Wee and Elsie Chen

docs.abstract: Tariffs would help steel and aluminum makers that President Trump championed. But manufacturers using their products may be in for harder times.
docs.snippet: Tariffs would help steel and aluminum makers that President Trump championed. But manufacturers using their products may be in for harder times.
docs.lead_paragraph: President Trump’s announcement that he planned to impose steep tariffs on imported steel and aluminum delighted some blue-collar industries he had championed. “Enthusiastic and gratified are probably understatements,” said Michael A. Bless, the president of Century Aluminum.

headline.main: Trump’s Tariff Plan Leaves Blue-Collar Winners and Losers
headline.print_headline: Plan for Tariffs Creates Divide In Trump Base

byline.original: By Natalie Kitroeff and Ana Swanson

docs.abstract: Regulators are on the verge of reducing a post-crisis requirement that banks maintain a certain amount of capital based on their total size. That has put regulators at odds.
docs.snippet: Regulators are on the verge of reducing a post-crisis requirement that banks maintain a certain amount of capital based on their total size. That has put regulators at odds.
docs.lead_paragraph: Bank regulators are on the cusp of weakening a rule put in place to prevent the nation’s biggest banks from causing another financial crisis, marking the first significant attempt by policymakers to fulfill President Trump’s promised regulatory rollback.

headline.main: Washington Wants to Weaken Bank Rules. Not Every Regulator Agrees.
headline.print_headline: Push to Ease Bank Rule Has Regulators at Odds

docs.abstract: Corporations and foreign leaders are pressing to meet with White House officials and hiring lawyers and lobbyists to push for exemptions that could be worth billions of dollars in trade.
docs.snippet: Corporations and foreign leaders are pressing to meet with White House officials and hiring lawyers and lobbyists to push for exemptions that could be worth billions of dollars in trade.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump’s decision to impose tariffs on imported steel and aluminum has prompted a stampede by foreign countries and companies and their American partners pressing for exemptions and exclusions that could be worth billions of dollars in trade.

headline.main: Trump’s Tariffs Set Off Storm of Lobbying
